randompassword

Generate a 30-character random password from the alphabet
`a-zA-Z0-9#.-` by reading bytes from /dev/urandom.

Defined as an alias in .zshrc:

  LC_ALL=C tr -cd '[:alnum:]' < /dev/urandom | fold -w30 | head -n1

(The actual alias also includes `#.-` in the allowed character set.)
The length is fixed at 30; use `mkpw` for a configurable length.
